Quick Installation Instructions
--

	# this creates a virtualenv named "OWL"
	virtualenv --distribute OWL

	# this puts the virtualenv on your path
	# sh:
		cd OWL
		. bin/activate

	# csh:
		cd OWL
		source bin/activate.csh

	# go to your owl source code
	cd .../owl

	# install the third party software that is required
	pip install -r requirements.txt

	# install OWL
	python setup.py install

	# see where the config files are located.
	python -m owl.config


For more in-depth instructions, please see docs/OWL_Installation_Notes.txt
